,"text":"Claiming a bounded precursor slice in existing telemetry modules. Plan: define a shared cross-subsystem telemetry record/adapters for runtime telemetry, connector canonical events, and policy audit entries so correlation IDs, severity/tier mapping, and sensitivity metadata converge before the full dashboard/query work lands. I’ll keep the slice out of active dependency owners’ files where possible and avoid assuming blocked upstream features are complete.","created_at":"2026-03-07T15:40:27Z"},{"id":1970,"issue_id":"ft-3681t.7.1","author":"PlumGate","text":"Implemented a bounded precursor slice in crates/frankenterm-core/src/runtime_telemetry.rs: added UnifiedTelemetryRecord + source adapters for RuntimeTelemetryEvent, CanonicalConnectorEvent, and RecorderAuditEntry with normalized reason_code/correlation/scope/tier/failure/sensitivity fields, safe structural attribute projection, and focused unit tests. Local rustfmt on the touched file passes. Full cargo validation is currently blocked by RCH infrastructure: rch workers probe --all reports RCH-E100 SSH connection failures for all configured workers even though rch check/doctor report healthy. I invoked rch exec for a targeted cargo test, it failed open to local cargo, and I terminated the local fallback immediately to respect the repo rule that cargo work must be offloaded via rch.","created_at":"2026-03-07T15:57:49Z"},{"id":2021,"issue_id":"ft-3681t.7.1","author":"GrayCitadel","text":"GrayCitadel taking a bounded follow-on slice in crates/frankenterm-core/src/runtime_health.rs. Rationale: bv still ranks ft-3681t.7.1 as one of the highest-impact active beads, PlumGate already landed UnifiedTelemetryRecord adapters in runtime_telemetry.rs, and the runtime health / incident surfaces still emit raw RuntimeTelemetryEvent data without also carrying the normalized telemetry contract. Scope: thread UnifiedTelemetryRecord into incident/robot-facing runtime health enrichment with focused tests, while avoiding activ